gomodel:SYNGO_2195  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: DGKB was enriched in postsynaptic density fractions.\nDGKB was localized in cell bodies, dendrites, and dendritic spines.\n\n26/01/2018 Pim\nAuthors note:\n- \"Most of the metal particles (arrowheads) are deposited in association with the cytoplasmic face of the plasma membrane in dendrites (A-C), spines (B) and soma (C)\"\n- \"At both types of synapses, immunogold particles for DGKβ were frequently observed at perisynaptic sites (Fig. 6F and G), thus revealing that DGKβ preferentially accumulates on the perisynaptic membrane at corticostriatal and thalamostriatal synapses.\"\nNote: With 'perisynaptic' the authors mean that DGKB is localized at the edge of the PSD. The biochemical data in Fig.7 suggest PSD association.. Experimental description: Materials and methods\nTissue and section preparation\nAdult Wistar rats (9 weeks old; Japan SLC) were used." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6194-9648" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5518-6584" ;
        dc:date           "2018-05-22" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_2195" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

